---
/**
 * Starlight `ThemeProvider` override. The site is dark-only, so force
 * `data-theme="dark"` and skip Starlight's OS/localStorage detection entirely.
 *
 * Without this, a visitor whose OS prefers light resolves to `data-theme="light"`,
 * and every Starlight component that uses a variable we don't override in
 * handbook.css (the mobile menu background `--sl-color-black`, the search modal,
 * the menu button) keeps Starlight's light value and renders white on our dark
 * surfaces. Inlined to avoid a flash of the wrong theme.
 */
---
<script is:inline>
document.documentElement.dataset.theme = "dark";
</script>
